column1: #Below is a text version of your DNA file.
#Genetic data is provided below as four TAB delimited columns.  Each line
#corresponds to a SNP.  Column one provides the SNP identifier (rsID where
#possible).  Column two contains the chromosome of the SNP
#using human reference build 37.1 coordinates.  Columns three and four
#contain the two alleles observed at this SNP (genotype).  The genotype is reported
#on the forward (+) strand (coding strand) with respect to the human reference.
**DISCLAIMER: this does not contain real human DNA**
